         <img id="content_contentImage" class="icon-image" alt="" src="/HealthTopics/glmedia/icons/getyourwell-womanvisiteveryyear.jpg">

           <div id="the-basics" class="topic_area"> 
            <h2 class="topic_area_title syndicate">The Basics</h2> 
            <div class="pages"> 
             <div class="page" id="page_787"> 
              <h2 class="topic_page_title">The Basics: <span>Overview</span></h2> 
              <div class="syndicate"> 
               <p>Schedule a well-woman visit with your doctor or nurse every year. The well-woman visit is an important&nbsp;way to&nbsp;help&nbsp;you stay healthy.</p>
               <p>Well-woman visits include a full checkup, separate from any other visit for sickness or injury.&nbsp;These visits focus on preventive care for women, which may include:</p>
               <ul>
                <li>Services, like shots, that improve your health by preventing diseases and other health problems</li>
                <li>Screenings, which are medical tests to check for diseases early when they may be easier to treat</li>
                <li>Education and counseling to help you make informed health decisions</li>
               </ul>
               <h3>What happens during a well-woman visit?</h3>
               <p>Your well-woman visit is a chance to focus on your overall health and wellness. There are 3 main goals for the visit:</p>
               <ol>
                <li>Documenting your health habits and history</li>
                <li>Getting a physical exam</li>
                <li>Setting health goals</li>
               </ol> 
              </div> 
              <div id="content_tabContentRepeater_areaContentRepeater_0_topic_navigation_0" class="topic_navigation clearfix"> 
               <div class="content_page_navigation clearfix"> 
                <span class="content_page_link right"> <span id="content_tabContentRepeater_areaContentRepeater_0_pageNextLabel_0" class="pageHeading">Next section</span> <a id="content_tabContentRepeater_areaContentRepeater_0_pageNext_0" class="button next" href="#the-basics_2">What to Expect</a> </span> 
                <span class="content_page_link left"> </span> 
                <span id="content_tabContentRepeater_areaContentRepeater_0_pageRange_0" class="content_page_range">1 of 5 sections</span> 
               </div> 
              </div> 
              <!-- /.topic_navigation --> 
             </div> 
             <div class="page" id="page_788"> 
              <h2 class="topic_page_title">The Basics: <span>What to Expect</span></h2> 
              <div class="syndicate"> 
               <h4>1. Health habits and history</h4>
               <p>Before your physical exam, the doctor or nurse will ask you to answer some questions about your overall health. These questions may cover topics like your:</p>
               <ul>
                <li>Medical history and family health history</li>
                <li>Sexual health and sexual partners</li>
                <li>Eating habits and physical activity</li>
                <li>Use of alcohol, tobacco, and other drugs</li>
                <li>Use of any medicines, vitamins, minerals, or herbs</li>
                <li>Mental health history, including depression</li>
                <li>Relationships and safety</li>
               </ul>
               <h4>2. Physical exam</h4>
               <p>The doctor or nurse will examine your body, which may include:</p>
               <ul>
                <li>Measuring your height and weight</li>
                <li>Calculating your body mass index (BMI) to see if you are at a healthy&nbsp;weight</li>
                <li>Checking your blood pressure</li>
                <li>Taking your temperature</li>
                <li>Doing a clinical breast exam (feeling your breasts and under your arms for lumps or other changes)</li>
                <li>Doing a pelvic exam (looking at your vagina and feeling around your pelvis)</li>
               </ul>
               <h4>3. Health goals</h4>
               <p>You and the doctor or nurse will talk about the next steps for helping you stay healthy. Together, you can decide which screenings or follow-up services are right for you.</p>
               <p>If you have health goals, like losing weight or quitting smoking, you and your doctor or nurse can make a plan to help you meet these goals.</p> 
              </div> 
              <div id="content_tabContentRepeater_areaContentRepeater_0_topic_navigation_1" class="topic_navigation clearfix"> 
               <div class="content_page_navigation clearfix"> 
                <span class="content_page_link right"> <span id="content_tabContentRepeater_areaContentRepeater_0_pageNextLabel_1" class="pageHeading">Next section</span> <a id="content_tabContentRepeater_areaContentRepeater_0_pageNext_1" class="button next" href="#take-action_1">Get Ready</a> </span>

                <span id="content_tabContentRepeater_areaContentRepeater_0_pageRange_1" class="content_page_range">2 of 5 sections</span>

           <div id="take-action" class="topic_area"> 
            <h2 class="topic_area_title syndicate">Take Action!</h2> 
            <div class="pages"> 
             <div class="page" id="page_790"> 
              <h2 class="topic_page_title">Take Action: <span>Get Ready</span></h2> 
              <div class="syndicate"> 
               <p>Take these steps to get the most out of your well-woman visit.</p>
               <h3>Know your family health history.</h3>
               <p>Your family's health history is an important part of your personal health record.&nbsp;<a href="https://familyhistory.hhs.gov/FHH/html/index.html" target="_blank"><strong>Use this family health history tool</strong></a>&nbsp;to keep track of conditions that run in your family.</p>
               <p>Be prepared to tell your doctor or nurse this information during your well-woman visit. Don't forget to share any new health problems in your family since your last visit.</p>
               <h3>Make a list of questions for your doctor.</h3>
               <p>This visit is a great time to ask the doctor or nurse any questions about:</p>
               <ul>
                <li>Birth control options</li>
                <li>Sexually transmitted diseases (STDs)</li>
                <li>Preparing to get pregnant</li>
                <li>Menopause</li>
                <li>Your safety and relationships</li>
                <li>Anxiety, depression, or other mental health issues</li>
                <li>Eating healthy</li>
                <li>Being more active</li>
               </ul>
               <p>Some important questions include:</p>
               <ul>
                <li>Do I need any important shots?</li>
                <li>How can I protect myself from HIV and other STDs?</li>
                <li><a href="/HealthTopics/Topic.aspx?id=87">Which form of birth control is right for me</a>?</li>
                <li>How do I know if my relationship is healthy and safe?</li>
                <li>Where can I get help for a mental health issue?</li>
                <li>What changes can I make to eat healthier?</li>
                <li>How can I be more physically active?</li>
               </ul>
               <p>Take a notepad or smart phone and write down the answers so you remember them later.</p> 
              </div> 
              <div id="content_tabContentRepeater_areaContentRepeater_1_topic_navigation_0" class="topic_navigation clearfix"> 
               <div class="content_page_navigation clearfix"> 
                <span class="content_page_link right"> <span id="content_tabContentRepeater_areaContentRepeater_1_pageNextLabel_0" class="pageHeading">Next section</span> <a id="content_tabContentRepeater_areaContentRepeater_1_pageNext_0" class="button next" href="#take-action_2">Ask about Screenings</a> </span> 
                <span class="content_page_link left"> <span id="content_tabContentRepeater_areaContentRepeater_1_pagePrevLabel_0" class="pageHeading">Previous section</span> <a id="content_tabContentRepeater_areaContentRepeater_1_pagePrev_0" class="button previous" href="#the-basics_2">What to Expect</a> </span> 
                <span id="content_tabContentRepeater_areaContentRepeater_1_pageRange_0" class="content_page_range">3 of 5 sections</span> 
               </div> 
              </div> 
              <!-- /.topic_navigation --> 
             </div> 
             <div class="page" id="page_791"> 
              <h2 class="topic_page_title">Take Action: <span>Ask about Screenings</span></h2> 
              <div class="syndicate"> 
               <h3>Talk with your doctor or nurse about which screenings you need.</h3>
               <p><a href="/HealthTopics/Topic.aspx?id=20">Getting screening tests</a> is one of the most important things you can do for your health. At your well-woman visit, the doctor or nurse may recommend screening you for:</p>
               <ul>
                <li>Certain types of cancer</li>
                <li>HPV (human papillomavirus, which can lead to <a href="/HealthTopics/Topic.aspx?id=13">cervical cancer</a>)</li>
                <li><a href="/HealthTopics/Topic.aspx?id=49">HIV</a> and other <a href="/HealthTopics/Topic.aspx?id=32"> sexually transmitted diseases (STDs)</a></li>
                <li><a href="/HealthTopics/Topic.aspx?id=11">High blood pressure</a>&nbsp;and <a href="/HealthTopics/Topic.aspx?id=14">cholesterol</a></li>
                <li><a href="/HealthTopics/Topic.aspx?id=73">Diabetes</a></li>
                <li><a href="/HealthTopics/Topic.aspx?id=12">Osteoporosis (weak bones)</a></li>
               </ul>
               <p>In addition to screenings, the doctor may sometimes recommend counseling for:</p>
               <ul>
                <li><a href="/HealthTopics/Topic.aspx?id=33">Depression</a></li>
                <li><a href="/HealthTopics/Topic.aspx?id=97">Relationship violence</a></li>
               </ul>
               <p><a href="/myhealthfinder/">Use the myhealthfinder tool</a> to find out which screening tests you may need.</p>
               <h4>What about cost?</h4>
               <p>Under the <a href="https://www.healthcare.gov/health-care-law-protections/" target="_blank">Affordable Care Act</a>, the health care reform law passed in 2010, most&nbsp;insurance plans now cover at least one well-woman visit per year at no cost to you. Plans must also cover some screenings and types of counseling.</p>
               <p>For more information about preventive services covered by the Affordable Care Act,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.healthcare.gov/coverage/preventive-care-benefits/" target="_blank">visit HealthCare.gov</a>.&nbsp;Contact your insurance provider to find out what’s covered by your plan.</p> 
              </div> 
              <div id="content_tabContentRepeater_areaContentRepeater_1_topic_navigation_1" class="topic_navigation clearfix"> 
               <div class="content_page_navigation clearfix"> 
                <span class="content_page_link right"> <span id="content_tabContentRepeater_areaContentRepeater_1_pageNextLabel_1" class="pageHeading">Next section</span> <a id="content_tabContentRepeater_areaContentRepeater_1_pageNext_1" class="button next" href="#take-action_3">Follow Up</a> </span> 
                <span class="content_page_link left"> <span id="content_tabContentRepeater_areaContentRepeater_1_pagePrevLabel_1" class="pageHeading">Previous section</span> <a id="content_tabContentRepeater_areaContentRepeater_1_pagePrev_1" class="button previous" href="#take-action_1">Get Ready</a> </span> 
                <span id="content_tabContentRepeater_areaContentRepeater_1_pageRange_1" class="content_page_range">4 of 5 sections</span> 
               </div> 
              </div> 
              <!-- /.topic_navigation --> 
             </div> 
             <div class="page" id="page_792"> 
              <h2 class="topic_page_title">Take Action: <span>Follow Up</span></h2> 
              <div class="syndicate"> 
               <h3>Follow up with the doctor or nurse after your visit.</h3>
               <p>During your well-woman visit, the doctor or nurse may recommend that you see a specialist or get certain screenings. Try to schedule these follow-up appointments before you leave the doctor’s office.</p>
               <p>If that’s not possible, make a note on your calendar to schedule your follow-up appointments. You can ask the doctor's office to write down the phone number and address for you.</p>
               <p><a href="/HealthTopics/Topic.aspx?id=78">Get more tips on taking an active role in your health care</a>.</p>
               <h3>Take steps to stay healthy all year.</h3>
               <p>There are things you can do every day to stay healthy. Find tips on:</p>
               <ul>
                <li><a href="/HealthTopics/Topic.aspx?id=22">Getting more physical activity</a></li>
                <li><a href="/HealthTopics/Topic.aspx?id=21">Eating healthy</a></li>
                <li><a href="/HealthTopics/Topic.aspx?id=45">Managing stress</a></li>
                <li><a href="/HealthTopics/Topic.aspx?id=24">Quitting smoking</a></li>
                <li><a href="/HealthTopics/Topic.aspx?id=25">Watching your weight</a></li>
                <li><a href="/HealthTopics/Topic.aspx?id=68">Getting enough sleep</a></li>
